    <stitle>HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS, AND BUMPER - PROSTAR&#8482; - REMOVE AND INSTALL PROCEDURES - GRILLE AND BUG SCREEN
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="Remove and Install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>GRILLE AND BUG SCREEN</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Grille and Bug Screen - Removal</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The grille should be removed with the hood in the closed position.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f0901111" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901111.webp" type="webp" scalefitwidth="312px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 13. Grille</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HOOD ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. TAB INSERTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. GRILLE</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. GRILLE MOUNT SCREWS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove four mount screws from the lower portion of the grille.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To remove the grille, lift the grille out to release the tabs from the tab inserts.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place the grille upside down on a padded surface to protect the finished surface of the
                    grille.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0901112" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901112.webp" type="webp" scalefitwidth="312px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 14. Bug Screen</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. BUG SCREEN CLIPS</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. GRILLE</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. BUG SCREEN</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. GRILLE TABS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Care must be taken when removing the bug screen clips to avoid breaking the tabs off the
                        grille.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove 15 bug screen clips from grille tabs by prying the bug screen clips loose from
                    the grille tabs.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lift the bug screen off the grille.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Grille and Bug Screen - Installation</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the bug screen on the grille making sure that all grille tabs are positioned
                    through the bug screen (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901112">Figure 14, Items 2, 3, and 4</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Secure the bug screen to the grille by installing 15 bug screen clips on the grille tabs
                    (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901112">Figure 14</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Before installing the grille, inspect the hood insert holes and ensure that all six insert
                        tabs are properly attached to the grille.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align grille insert tabs with the hood insert holes ((
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901111">Figure 13, Items 2 and 3</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With the palm of your hand, press the grille at all six insert tab locations to seat
                    grille onto the hood (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901111">Figure 13, Items 1, 2, and 3</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install four mount screws in bottom of grille (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901111">Figure 13, Items 3 and 4</hotlnk>). Torque screws to 4 to 5 lbf-ft (5 to 7
                    N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
